cs.FL, cs.CL, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.GR

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the language O_2 and its classification as an MCFL (Multiple Context-Free Language).
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper discusses the relation between extreme free word order and classes of grammars used to describe the syntax of natural language.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper may involve algorithms or data structures related to parsing or recognizing MCFLs.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possibility as the paper mentions concepts specific to two-dimensional geometry, although it also states that the proof avoids such concepts.
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a less likely possibility as the paper mentions two-dimensional geometry, but it is not the main focus of the paper.
